sum-recurrence constant is `K_eff = 9792/|p'(z₁)| < 9792 · 35 =
342,720` (using `1/|p'(z₁)| < 35`). Iterating this recurrence yields
the geometric upper bound `Σ_{i ≤ m} |a_i| ≤ |c₀|·(1 + K_eff)^m`,
which feeds directly into the ratio-test convergence radius lower
bound `r ≥ 1/(1 + K_eff)`. -/
lemma aperyConifold_frobenius_Z_succ_le_sum (c₀ : ℝ) (m : ℕ) (hm : 6 ≤ m) :
